<i>Can you see it? Look closer.</i>

01:53.546 --> 01:55.571
(SINGING) <i>Don't look away</i>

01:55.648 --> 01:57.741
<i>Don't run away</i>

01:57.817 --> 02:01.412
<i>Hey, baby, it's only life</i>

02:01.488 --> 02:03.456
<i>Don't lose your faith</i>

02:03.523 --> 02:05.650
<i>Don't run away</i>

02:05.725 --> 02:10.958
<i>Hey, baby, it's only life</i>

02:12.365 --> 02:14.162
Cut. Cut!

02:14.234 --> 02:17.670
Great. Really great work, Mia. Excellent.
Thank you guys very much.

02:17.737 --> 02:19.728
We can check that and move on.

02:19.806 --> 02:21.296
- Hey. How crazy is this?
- Hey.

02:21.374 --> 02:23.968
- It looks just like your classroom, right?
- I know, it's so crazy.

02:24.043 --> 02:27.274
- All right, gate's good. Let's move on.
- Thank you.

02:27.347 --> 02:28.871
I kind of need to get out of here.

02:28.948 --> 02:30.745
I don't know if you guys need me
for close-ups.

02:30.817 --> 02:33.718
- No, no, no. You're good.
- Okay. All right, see you.

02:33.786 --> 02:35.276
Oh, Haley.

02:35.421 --> 02:36.410
Um...

02:37.557 --> 02:40.890
Okay, about the whole
Lucas engagement thing, I just...

02:40.960 --> 02:43.394
- You gotta let him go, Peyton.
- I know.

02:43.930 --> 02:45.488
It's just hard.

02:46.966 --> 02:49.696
You'll be okay. I'll see you at the game.

02:52.372 --> 02:54.738
This is so awesome. What's next?

02:55.542 --> 02:57.169
We go hand-held.

02:59.179 --> 03:03.309
MOUTH: Local boys make good.
A new era dawns.

03:04.984 --> 03:06.645
Come on, find the story.

03:06.719 --> 03:08.209
(SKILLS LAUGHING)

03:08.288 --> 03:09.721
Tonight's the big night, baby.

03:09.789 --> 03:13.919
First game of the season and broadcasting
debut for Marvin McFadden.

03:13.993 --> 03:16.291
It's just a taped segment.
I'm not even sure they're gonna run it.

03:16.362 --> 03:17.488
Man, they gonna run it.

03:17.564 --> 03:20.931
Look, you gonna throw down so hard,
they gonna have to run it.

03:21.000 --> 03:22.228
Got an angle, right?

03:22.302 --> 03:25.396
Yeah, I'm thinking "Former state
champions take over."

03:25.471 --> 03:26.631
Something like that.

03:26.739 --> 03:30.573
Yeah, that's all good.
Well, look, if you need anything, I got you.

03:30.643 --> 03:32.304
All-access, baby.

03:36.849 --> 03:41.650
Hey, Mouth. Relax, dawg.
You gonna do great, all right?

03:50.697 --> 03:52.824
Hey, sorry. I'll just be one more minute.

03:52.899 --> 03:57.029
I've never seen Jamie so keyed-up.
He's so excited about this game.

04:01.874 --> 04:05.366
- Everything all right?
- I have to tell you something.

04:08.214 --> 04:09.909
It's about Carrie.

04:10.483 --> 04:13.316
I should probably be the one to tell her.

04:13.453 --> 04:15.944
I have to give my two weeks' notice.

04:16.488 --> 04:18.582
(STAMMERING) Why?

04:18.658 --> 04:22.617
Because I got accepted to a graduate
program that I thought I couldn't afford,

04:22.695 --> 04:27.132
but I got a last-minute scholarship offer,
and I think I have to take it.

04:28.301 --> 04:31.327
Well, of course you do. Congratulations.

04:31.404 --> 04:34.840
We're gonna miss you.
I hope Jamie doesn't take it too hard.

04:34.907 --> 04:38.468
Yeah, I'm gonna miss you, too.
More than you know.

04:44.217 --> 04:45.548
Hey, Luke.

04:47.320 --> 04:49.447
You working on the game plan?

04:49.522 --> 04:53.356
Actually, I was just thinking about Keith.

04:54.794 --> 04:57.092
Wishing he were here, you know?

04:58.164 --> 05:00.928
I've been thinking about Jimmy all week.

05:02.101 --> 05:05.400
What I wouldn't give to trade this day
for that one.

05:08.875 --> 05:12.777
I see they took Dan's jersey down
in the gym. I'm glad.

05:17.350 --> 05:19.147
Jimmy'd be proud of you.

05:19.218 --> 05:21.448
Thanks. You, too.

05:25.391 --> 05:27.291
Good luck, Luke.

05:27.360 --> 05:29.021
Thanks, Mouth. You, too.

05:35.702 --> 05:38.330
Oh, Keith, please help me out tonight.

05:49.248 --> 05:51.876
<i>WOMAN: (SINGING)</i>
<i>You hold your head up to the sky</i>

05:51.951 --> 05:56.513
<i>You say, what kind of blue are you?</i>

05:57.190 --> 05:59.317
<i>Are you?</i>

06:00.326 --> 06:03.056
<i>Then you ride your pony round and round</i>

06:03.129 --> 06:08.066
<i>It's digging a hole right through</i>

06:09.168 --> 06:12.331
- So, what you think, ball? It's good?
- Yeah, it's good.

06:12.739 --> 06:14.832
(PONY <i>CONTINUES PLA YING)</i>

06:15.508 --> 06:16.497
Yeah.

06:22.582 --> 06:23.571
Yeah!

06:27.353 --> 06:30.049
Hey, Peyton, is that really
who you used to be?

06:30.123 --> 06:32.057
Yep, that's me. Come on.

06:32.125 --> 06:33.888
Wow. You were really cool.
What happened?

06:33.960 --> 06:35.291
Watch it.

06:35.361 --> 06:38.159
So tell me again, we're going to see the
team that your ex-boyfriend coaches,

06:38.231 --> 06:40.597
but now he's engaged
to Haley's friend, right?

06:40.666 --> 06:44.067
Okay. You wanna see
where I went to high school or not?

06:44.137 --> 06:48.039
No, totally. I just wanna know
who we hate before we get there.

06:51.244 --> 06:53.371
PEYTON: You see the girl showing off
her cheap-ass engagement ring

06:53.446 --> 06:55.311
to my best friend?

06:55.381 --> 06:57.212
Yeah. Lindsey, right?

06:58.518 --> 07:00.281
That's who we hate.

07:06.125 --> 07:07.990
She knows exactly what she's doing.

07:08.060 --> 07:10.426
I cannot believe that Lindsey
invited Brooke to the game.

07:10.496 --> 07:11.963
I mean, it's bad enough she's got Lucas,

07:12.031 --> 07:14.056
but now she's got to
snake in on my friends, too?

07:14.133 --> 07:16.465
You know, I once put a hex on a girl
I hated, and it totally worked.

07:16.536 --> 07:18.367
Really? Maybe you could give
her, like, a horrible rash

07:18.438 --> 07:19.666
or something for the wedding.

07:19.739 --> 07:21.604
Totally. So are we gonna go back or what?

07:21.674 --> 07:23.938
I mean, I'm pretty excited
about this catfight.

07:24.010 --> 07:25.477
Okay, do you want to see
the place where I got shot

07:25.545 --> 07:28.639
- and almost bled to death or what?
- The catfight can wait.

07:30.716 --> 07:33.344
- Hey, we saved you a seat.
- Hi, thank you so much.

07:33.453 --> 07:36.513
Oh, I can't wait to get
a good shot of Jamie...

07:36.589 --> 07:39.149
With my camera that I don't have.
It's in my classroom.

07:39.225 --> 07:40.783
Can we go with you?

07:40.860 --> 07:43.624
I'm dying to see teacher girl's classroom.

07:43.696 --> 07:45.425
All right. Come on.

07:47.099 --> 07:50.091
(DIRTY SOUTH HUSTLA <i>PLA YING)</i>

07:54.507 --> 07:56.839
LUKE: All right, let's go. Listen up.

07:59.512 --> 08:02.140
Four years ago, we won
a state championship.

08:02.215 --> 08:04.911
And since then,
there's been a lot of losing.

08:04.984 --> 08:08.613
But this is a new team,
and this is your house.

08:08.688 --> 08:10.178
(ALL AGREEING)

08:10.256 --> 08:12.247
- Good teams win at home.
- Every game.

08:12.325 --> 08:13.690
Every game.

08:14.193 --> 08:16.161
And this is a good team.

08:17.396 --> 08:20.559
Believe in that. Believe in each other.

08:22.835 --> 08:24.996
It all starts tonight, boys.

08:25.071 --> 08:26.971
(PLAYERS CHATTERING)

08:27.039 --> 08:30.736
A new team deserves a new look.

08:32.010 --> 08:35.503
(PLAYERS EX CLAIMING)

08:36.782 --> 08:40.775
You should win half of your games
just for looking so damn good.

08:41.754 --> 08:43.381
And Jamie Scott.

08:45.925 --> 08:48.120
You better suit up, too, son.

08:50.329 --> 08:53.264
If Q's hand isn't right, we might need you.

08:53.933 --> 08:59.132
PLAYERS: Go, Jamie. Go, Jamie. Go, Jamie.
Hey. Go, Jamie. Hey.

08:59.205 --> 09:03.301
Go, Jamie. Go, Jamie. Hey. Go, Jamie.
Hey. Go, Jamie.

09:04.844 --> 09:07.108
<i>(BRING ITON</i> PLAYING)

09:16.155 --> 09:20.421
<i>I'm gonna walk my faith</i>
<i>Gonna raise my song</i>

09:22.995 --> 09:25.361
<i>Bring it on</i>

09:26.132 --> 09:28.965
<i>Bring it on</i>

09:29.368 --> 09:32.565
This is so weird. I feel like I haven't
walked these halls in 20 years.

09:32.638 --> 09:35.334
- Yeah?
- Hey...

09:35.408 --> 09:36.932
Isn't that Mia?

09:37.843 --> 09:42.109
LINDSEY: Okay.
BROOKE: Yeah.

09:44.517 --> 09:47.645
- Mia? What are you doing here?
- Hey.

09:51.557 --> 09:53.149
Oh, hey, Peyton.

09:53.225 --> 09:57.389
Hey, check it out. It's my old friends,
Brooke and Haley, and their

09:57.797 --> 09:59.264
new pal, Lindsey.

09:59.332 --> 10:01.493
Peyton, we made plans for tonight
before you...

10:01.567 --> 10:03.262
Before you called me a bitch.

10:03.336 --> 10:07.170
Bitch? No. No, I did not call you a bitch.

10:07.473 --> 10:09.498
I said I didn't like you.

10:09.842 --> 10:11.810
- Peyton...
- No, you don't have to make apologies

10:11.877 --> 10:14.744
to her, just like I'm not apologizing
because I'm engaged to Lucas

10:14.814 --> 10:16.304
and she's not.

10:17.149 --> 10:19.947
You know, I really was gonna
try to be nice to you,

10:20.019 --> 10:21.884
but I think that's officially over.

10:21.954 --> 10:23.751
- Works for me.
- Great.

10:24.924 --> 10:27.051
- I'm gonna head back.
- Hey.

10:27.159 --> 10:29.354
If you get tired dragging
that fat ass of yours back to the gym

10:29.428 --> 10:33.159
- there is a water fountain down the hall.
- Whatever, you bulimic bitch.

10:33.265 --> 10:35.460
(BANGING)

10:38.237 --> 10:40.000
I can't. There's no handle.

10:40.072 --> 10:41.334
(LAUGHS)

10:43.776 --> 10:46.176
They're fixing them over the weekend.

10:46.245 --> 10:49.612
- So, what's that mean?
- I think it means we're stuck.

10:54.353 --> 10:57.789
Help. Help. Somebody.

10:58.724 --> 11:01.784
- Help us!
- Help us. Somebody...

11:02.061 --> 11:03.926
(GIRLS SCREAMING)

11:15.675 --> 11:21.136
Somebody, please.
Somebody get us out of here. Help!

11:22.248 --> 11:24.910
Lindsey, nobody's gonna hear you.
They're all at the game.

11:24.984 --> 11:28.545
We cannot be locked in here.
I am totally claustrophobic.

11:28.921 --> 11:31.151
But it's, like, a huge library.

11:31.223 --> 11:34.283
- It's the locked-in part.
- Just relax. You'll be okay.

11:34.360 --> 11:37.386
Okay, they're fixing all the other doors.
No handles.

11:37.463 --> 11:39.590
And the phones seem to be out.

11:39.665 --> 11:41.826
Yeah. All the calls will go
through the office. Nobody's answering.

11:41.901 --> 11:44.734
All right. Does anybody have cell phone
reception? 'Cause I got nothing.

11:44.804 --> 11:46.032
I don't.

11:47.039 --> 11:50.031
Nobody ever gets cell phone
reception in here.

11:50.476 --> 11:53.309
Except for me, 'cause the world loves me.

11:53.412 --> 11:57.280
I'm gonna call Mouth.
I'll have us out of here in two seconds.

11:58.150 --> 12:00.380
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

12:04.824 --> 12:07.850
<i>ON VOICEMAIL: Hey, this is Mouth.</i>
<i>Please leave me a message.</i>

12:10.129 --> 12:11.153
It went to voicemail.

12:11.230 --> 12:14.495
Well, there's gotta be somebody else
we can call to get out of here.

12:14.567 --> 12:15.932
Call the police. 911.

12:16.001 --> 12:18.094
PEYTON: Oh, really? There's someone
out there getting murdered

12:18.170 --> 12:21.071
and we're gonna bother the police?
No. There is somebody that we know

12:21.140 --> 12:23.973
who's not coaching
or playing in this game.

12:24.243 --> 12:26.507
Don't ask me. I just moved here.

12:26.579 --> 12:27.773
Brooke.

12:28.047 --> 12:29.810
- I don't want to.
- Brooke.

12:29.882 --> 12:31.372
I don't even know his number.

12:31.450 --> 12:32.883
What's going on?
What are you talking about?

12:32.952 --> 12:35.785
Brooke's gonna call Owen,
her new bartender crush, to get us out.

12:35.855 --> 12:39.621
- I am not. It's too soon.
- Brooke, we're gonna miss the game.

12:39.692 --> 12:43.719
I don't want to call him.
It violates all the rules of dating etiquette.

12:43.796 --> 12:46.458
I am gonna look desperate,
he has to do us a favor

12:46.532 --> 12:49.831
- and then he can make fun of me for it.
- Oh, my God.

12:51.303 --> 12:55.205
Fine. I will call him,
but if he does not sleep with me after this,

12:55.274 --> 12:57.606
it is your fault. All of you.

12:57.676 --> 12:59.769
I think I'm okay with that.

13:00.846 --> 13:02.074
(PHONE BEEPING)

13:02.314 --> 13:03.372
(LAUGHS)

13:03.449 --> 13:04.438
What?

13:04.517 --> 13:06.781
- My battery just died. It's great.
- What?

13:06.852 --> 13:09.844
- Isn't that great?
- Brooke, we're stuck.

13:10.289 --> 13:11.984
Stuck is not good.

13:12.424 --> 13:15.154
HAYLEY: Come, come sit down
for a second, okay?

13:17.029 --> 13:19.054
All right, just breathe and close your eyes

13:19.131 --> 13:22.225
and try and think of a place
that makes you happy and calm.

13:22.301 --> 13:24.531
You got it? Where are you?

13:24.603 --> 13:28.039
I'm with my dad.
We're walking near Walden Pond. It's fall.

13:28.107 --> 13:31.668
- The leaves are changing.
- You're not here. You're there.

13:32.011 --> 13:33.239
Better?

13:35.080 --> 13:36.809
- Yeah.
- Okay.

13:37.316 --> 13:39.443
Hey, Mia, are you okay?

13:39.985 --> 13:43.182
I'm great.
I actually think this is kinda awesome.

13:43.622 --> 13:46.455
I can finally get to know you guys.
I have questions.

13:46.525 --> 13:48.220
No. Now is not the time.

13:48.294 --> 13:51.127
Oh, come on.
You guys totally fascinate me.

13:51.497 --> 13:53.931
- Especially you, Brooke.
- Really?

13:54.366 --> 13:57.426
Well, in that case, ask away, my dear.

13:57.937 --> 14:00.838
Okay. Like, you're really successful, right?

14:00.906 --> 14:04.171
- Like, really cool and rich?
- Yes, yes and yes.

14:05.211 --> 14:09.807
So why do you let that horrible stink
of a mom boss you around all the time?

14:11.450 --> 14:13.714
You should quit being so nosy.

14:14.787 --> 14:16.618
Come on, Brooke.
You know she's not nice.

14:16.689 --> 14:20.557
- I'm not talking about my mom.
- Hey. She doesn't appreciate you.

14:20.626 --> 14:24.392
- She is my mother, all right?
- That doesn't make it right.

14:24.797 --> 14:28.164
Okay. It's time for the two new kids
to stay the hell out of it,

14:28.234 --> 14:31.601
and as for you two,
I expect you both to understand.

14:33.005 --> 14:36.463
- What's that supposed to mean?
- You know what it means.

14:36.942 --> 14:39.502
Neither of your moms were around,
at least not in all the time

14:39.578 --> 14:41.808
that I've been friends with you.

14:41.881 --> 14:45.317
And I'm sorry for that, but what if you had
a chance to have them back in your lives?

14:45.384 --> 14:47.147
Brooke, I would love to have them back,

14:47.219 --> 14:50.120
both of them, all right? But I would hope
that they'd be coming back

14:50.189 --> 14:52.851
because they love me,
not because they wanted to run my label.

14:52.925 --> 14:55.792
- Oh, the label I financed?
- No, easy. I'm with you.

14:55.861 --> 14:59.524
Now. You are with me now, Peyton,

14:59.732 --> 15:03.566
but for the last four years,
my mom has been with me every day

15:03.636 --> 15:05.627
helping me create a pretty great company.

15:05.704 --> 15:07.865
That's not true.

15:09.108 --> 15:12.805
I was with you when you created that
pretty great company, and so was Peyton.

15:12.878 --> 15:16.336
Maybe your mom made it bigger,
but you created it all by yourself.

15:16.415 --> 15:20.852
You did. You made it great before your
mom even stepped into the picture.

15:21.020 --> 15:22.715
You guys don't know anything about it.

15:22.788 --> 15:25.484
Maybe not, but I do know
that a mother's love is unconditional,

15:25.557 --> 15:27.286
and you don't have to earn it,
and you don't have to

15:27.359 --> 15:29.850
design a fashion label to keep it.

15:30.329 --> 15:31.728
It just is.

15:32.264 --> 15:34.664
You don't know anything about it.

15:52.584 --> 15:53.744
You okay?

15:53.819 --> 15:56.413
I'm thinking I can break this window.

15:57.022 --> 15:59.490
Lindsey, somebody's gonna come
get us out of here.

15:59.558 --> 16:02.254
- I can do it.
- No... Oh... Okay.

16:02.328 --> 16:03.955
(SCREAMS)

16:05.364 --> 16:07.059
(PANTING)

16:07.132 --> 16:09.794
Jeez, that chair is really heavy.

16:17.009 --> 16:18.135
Hey.

16:20.179 --> 16:23.114
Check it out.
I found librarian Glaufelte's stash.

16:23.182 --> 16:26.242
We always knew she was boozy.
Want some?

16:31.056 --> 16:32.648
Whatcha reading?

16:35.427 --> 16:36.758
<i>B. Davis.</i>

16:41.433 --> 16:43.663
She came up with this, Peyton.

16:44.970 --> 16:49.339
The magazine, the high-end clientele,
Victoria did all of it.

16:50.175 --> 16:54.339
I know. But it's not called <i>V. Davis,</i> is it?

16:59.818 --> 17:03.345
All those years growing up,
I just wanted her to see me.

17:04.522 --> 17:08.983
To see me and appreciate me
and maybe love me.

17:12.931 --> 17:17.925
And now that I have it, even if it's for
the wrong reasons, it's hard to let it go.

17:20.105 --> 17:22.096
Can you understand that?

17:24.443 --> 17:25.535
Yeah.

17:32.451 --> 17:33.440
This is terrible.

17:33.519 --> 17:36.283
It's Lucas' first game,
we're stuck in this stupid library.

17:36.355 --> 17:39.324
- Ah, I wish we knew the score.
- Ravens down by eight.

17:39.491 --> 17:42.483
Wait, let me refresh. Ravens down by ten.

17:43.529 --> 17:45.497
- Are you online?
- Yeah.

17:46.899 --> 17:48.594
Brooke, Peyton, come here.
We got Internet.

17:48.667 --> 17:50.931
Hey, you guys want to see me at Tric?

17:51.003 --> 17:53.494
Okay, there's got to be a way
we can use this to get out.

17:53.572 --> 17:56.769
Or at least order a pizza.
I'm starving. No, that's it.

17:56.842 --> 17:58.434
Do we need to be thinking
about food right now?

17:58.510 --> 18:01.343
No, we order pizza online. We have it
delivered here so we can get out.

18:01.413 --> 18:03.506
- Oh.
- Okay, Blackwell's Pizzeria...

18:03.582 --> 18:07.985
They are open.
You can order online, and they deliver.

18:08.053 --> 18:09.543
- Yes.
- Nice.

18:10.856 --> 18:13.188
- So, what are we getting?
- What?

18:13.425 --> 18:15.154
What kind of pizza?

18:15.561 --> 18:17.927
- I don't know. Mushroom and sausage.
- Oh, no mushroom, please, I...

18:17.996 --> 18:19.964
- Brooke.
- Actually, I'm totally with Brooke.

18:20.032 --> 18:21.897
- Canadian bacon?
- Canadian bacon. Extra cheese.

18:21.967 --> 18:23.525
- You guys, seriously...
- Just order the damn pizza.

18:23.602 --> 18:25.763
- Okay. Do not yell at me.
- I'll yell at you if I want.

18:25.838 --> 18:28.102
Just order it. Freaking sausage,
freaking Canadian bacon

18:28.173 --> 18:29.902
freaking mushroom,
I wanna get the hell out of here.

18:29.975 --> 18:31.772
We all want to get the hell out of here,
okay?

18:31.844 --> 18:34.278
- Don't yell at me.
- HAYLEY: Calm down. God.

18:37.216 --> 18:38.843
Just no mushroom.

18:41.553 --> 18:44.420
There. It's ordered. Are we all happy now?

18:45.557 --> 18:46.683
What'd we get?

18:46.758 --> 18:49.192
No mushroom, Brooke, okay?
No mush, no room, no mushroom!

18:49.261 --> 18:51.422
Okay. Everybody, please relax, okay?
The pizza guy's gonna come,

18:51.497 --> 18:53.556
he's gonna let us out, and maybe
we'll make the end of the game,

18:53.632 --> 18:56.430
so in the meantime,
everybody just calm down.

19:03.809 --> 19:06.642
You did a great job with my record, Haley.

19:07.212 --> 19:08.543
Thank you.

19:09.548 --> 19:11.345
(LAUGHS)

19:11.416 --> 19:13.145
Where did that come from?

19:13.218 --> 19:15.846
I don't know. I just think we tear each
other down enough, you know?

19:15.921 --> 19:18.856
And sometimes you should tell people
the things that you love about 'em,

19:18.924 --> 19:22.860
like something they're really great at
or a quality they have that you admire,

19:22.928 --> 19:25.863
and I don't know,
you did a really good job.

19:26.431 --> 19:29.161
Courage. Haley's courageous.

19:29.401 --> 19:32.393
- And strong.
- And kind.

19:33.138 --> 19:35.436
See, don't you feel
like you're pretty awesome now?

19:35.507 --> 19:37.668
Yeah, I kinda do.

19:37.743 --> 19:40.803
- Okay, do me. What's great about me?
- Your voice. It's an amazing gift.

19:40.879 --> 19:43.939
- The fact that you came up with this game.
- Your boobs.

19:44.049 --> 19:47.815
And your lips. I would kill for lips like that.
You know?

19:47.886 --> 19:50.184
And you've got good legs.
It's like a whole...

19:50.255 --> 19:53.224
(LAUGHS) Okay. Before this turns into
a women-in-prison film,

19:53.292 --> 19:55.522
I think we should move on.

19:56.662 --> 19:59.825
Lindsey. Your eyes are, like, not even fair.

20:00.465 --> 20:02.296
You're also one of the smartest people
I know.

20:02.367 --> 20:04.392
- I am not.
- And you're classy.

20:04.469 --> 20:05.834
You guys...

20:08.640 --> 20:12.804
Peyton, isn't there something nice
you'd like to say about Lindsey?

20:16.548 --> 20:18.709
She's got decent taste in men.

20:22.354 --> 20:23.946
This game sucks.

20:26.558 --> 20:28.617
I'm intimidated by Peyton.

20:31.830 --> 20:36.790
I spent a year editing a book
that was basically a love letter to her.

20:37.736 --> 20:41.433
I watched how caring and meticulous
Lucas was with the words

20:41.506 --> 20:44.942
he chose for her,
like he was still holding on to her.

20:51.917 --> 20:54.147
Sometimes I think he still is.

20:58.090 --> 21:00.456
Which is why he proposed to you, right?

21:00.692 --> 21:02.523
Yeah, I can see that.

21:04.663 --> 21:06.722
God, I hate this library.

21:15.307 --> 21:16.865
- I found it.
- A way out?

21:16.942 --> 21:19.376
No. Lucas' book. I never read it.

21:26.652 --> 21:28.643
They replaced the carpet.

21:32.758 --> 21:36.421
This is where Lucas and I hid out
during the school shooting,

21:36.495 --> 21:39.328
but they changed the carpet.
It doesn't match.

21:40.499 --> 21:43.491
I'm not gonna tell you
how to be with Lindsey.

21:44.403 --> 21:46.837
But most of your life,
I've known you to take the high road.

21:46.905 --> 21:52.969
I know, Brooke. I'm so sick
of looking at her and her precious ring.

21:55.180 --> 21:57.307
You mean your precious ring?

22:02.154 --> 22:03.416
(BOTH LAUGHING)

22:03.488 --> 22:04.955
All right. One more.

22:05.424 --> 22:06.891
(BOTH EX CLAIMING)

22:07.526 --> 22:09.551
Score me. Score me, Haley.

22:10.829 --> 22:13.297
Ravens are down by nine. Halftime.

22:14.966 --> 22:16.763
Wait. Hold on.

22:17.135 --> 22:20.571
Are you telling me Lucas slept with
Peyton, Brooke, and you, Lindsey?

22:20.639 --> 22:22.937
Yeah. Not all at the same time.

22:23.008 --> 22:24.498
(LAUGHING)

22:24.576 --> 22:26.806
Jeez, Haley, you sure you never
got in on that?

22:26.878 --> 22:28.436
Ew, he's like my brother.

22:28.513 --> 22:31.243
I'm just saying. Jamie looks a lot like him.

22:31.316 --> 22:32.749
Ah, they're like twins.

22:32.818 --> 22:35.013
- They are not.
- Yes, they are.

22:35.854 --> 22:38.880
And what inbred moron
is taking so long with our pizza?

22:39.791 --> 22:42.919
(NEVER EVEN TOLD ME HER NAME
<i>PLA YING)</i>

22:55.240 --> 22:57.037
Well, well, well.

23:00.946 --> 23:03.608
Oh, my God,
4,000 hits for my video at Tric.

23:03.682 --> 23:06.981
Listen to these comments.
"You rock. Where can I buy this?"

23:07.052 --> 23:08.451
That's really great, Mia.

23:08.520 --> 23:12.320
"This song is awesome.
I'd love to see this chick naked."

23:13.091 --> 23:15.821
- Ew.
- It's just one comment.

23:15.894 --> 23:17.054
No, wait, there's more.

23:17.129 --> 23:19.529
"Another pop princess
who can't sing or play.

23:19.598 --> 23:21.998
"She looks like she smells like dirty feet"?

23:22.067 --> 23:23.898
- What's wrong with people?
- You need to stop.

23:23.969 --> 23:25.937
Do you know what people
use the Internet for?

23:26.004 --> 23:27.665
- Porn and complaining.
- Yep.

23:27.739 --> 23:31.004
But that's so not fair. They have to know
there's somebody reading this.

23:31.076 --> 23:33.874
It's the easiest thing in the world
to tear down somebody's work.

23:33.945 --> 23:37.574
The hard part is actually creating it.
It's criticism versus creation.

23:37.649 --> 23:39.310
Do you love making music?

23:39.384 --> 23:43.480
- Yeah.
- Okay, so the rest doesn't matter.

23:43.588 --> 23:46.580
Easy for you to say.
They didn't say you smell like feet.

23:46.658 --> 23:48.751
Oh, sticks and stones, Mia.

23:49.995 --> 23:52.156
Oh, right. This coming from the girl
that couldn't handle it

23:52.230 --> 23:54.494
when I said I didn't like her.

23:54.933 --> 23:59.029
Okay. Let's just check the scorecard
on this one, Miss "Pity me."

23:59.137 --> 24:02.470
You dated the guy two years ago,
you disappeared

24:02.541 --> 24:05.533
then you come back
and expect him to drop everything

24:05.610 --> 24:09.137
for the love of your bony, jobless ass.
W.T. F?

24:09.214 --> 24:10.977
Okay, D.U.I.

24:11.049 --> 24:13.244
Nice work, Haley.
Better save old drinky here

24:13.318 --> 24:15.912
before I kick her spoiled ass
all the way back to Walden Pond.

24:15.987 --> 24:17.750
- Oh, yeah?
- Yeah.

24:17.823 --> 24:21.054
Guess this is the second time
you'll be bleeding all over this library.

24:21.126 --> 24:23.720
You think that's funny?
You think that's funny?

24:23.795 --> 24:25.854
(ALL SHOUTING)

24:25.931 --> 24:29.128
Tim Smith is in the lib-ra-zee!

24:29.634 --> 24:30.999
Oh, my God.

24:31.770 --> 24:34.170
- Oh, my God.
- Oh, my God. Brooke.

24:34.239 --> 24:37.003
No! No. No, no.

24:37.108 --> 24:38.473
- Put me down.
- It's so good to see...

24:38.543 --> 24:41.944
No. You idiot! The door is locked.

24:42.013 --> 24:44.004
No, it's not. I just walked in, Brooke.

24:44.082 --> 24:46.141
From the outside, Tim.

24:46.218 --> 24:48.516
The door is locked from the outside.

24:48.587 --> 24:50.350
We cannot get out.

24:50.856 --> 24:52.323
Girl, chill.

24:52.791 --> 24:57.194
I'll just call somebody at the pizza place
and have them send someone...

24:57.696 --> 24:59.561
- I left my phone in my scooter.
- Oh?

24:59.631 --> 25:01.895
Motorcycle. It's a motorcycle.

25:05.570 --> 25:08.767
Well, since we're locked in here all alone,

25:10.675 --> 25:14.771
who wants a piece? Extra sausage.

25:17.282 --> 25:20.945
Ravens trail by nine. Sold-out crowd.

25:22.754 --> 25:26.417
Come on, Mouth.
There's a great story here. Find it.

25:40.005 --> 25:42.235
BROOKE: Oh, my God. Please don't fall.

25:44.776 --> 25:46.368
(GIRLS LAUGHING)

25:46.811 --> 25:51.111
If you had to eat any part of a person
to stay alive, what would you eat?

25:51.182 --> 25:52.308
What?

25:52.584 --> 25:56.543
Like, I don't know,
say we ran out of food and Haley died.

25:56.621 --> 25:58.088
Thanks a lot.

25:58.990 --> 26:01.254
Okay, someone else dies,
and we need to survive.

26:01.326 --> 26:03.317
- What do you eat?
- I know what I'm starting with.

26:03.395 --> 26:06.296
- Don't say it, perv.
- Love handles.

26:06.865 --> 26:10.198
I'd make, like, beef jerky
out of their love handles.

26:11.269 --> 26:12.702
You could snack on that for days.

26:12.771 --> 26:16.537
Ew. I so would not eat
someone's love handles.

26:16.608 --> 26:19.076
Okay. Well, you're gonna starve,
and we're all gonna eat you, then.

26:19.144 --> 26:21.044
No one gonna's eat me, either.

26:21.112 --> 26:22.136
No.

26:24.115 --> 26:27.084
You know, I could eat your neck
like a vampire.

26:27.152 --> 26:29.416
- You guys, seriously.
- What's the big deal?

26:29.487 --> 26:30.954
You're dead, and I'm hungry.

26:31.022 --> 26:34.549
- Yeah, don't you want us to live?
- We're hungry, Brooke.

26:35.427 --> 26:36.724
Please.

26:36.795 --> 26:41.858
Okay. Chow down, but I am gonna haunt
each and every one of you.

26:44.436 --> 26:45.960
I believe in ghosts.

26:46.037 --> 26:47.902
- Totally.
- Yeah, don't even get me started.

26:47.973 --> 26:50.271
I don't know.
Do you believe in ghosts, Linds?

26:51.676 --> 26:53.644
I think if someone dies suddenly,

26:53.712 --> 26:57.170
especially before their time,
maybe they get confused.

26:57.248 --> 26:59.648
They don't know to leave a place.

27:01.052 --> 27:03.577
You think they're still here, then?

27:05.724 --> 27:07.715
Jimmy Edwards and Keith?

27:18.970 --> 27:23.407
I wish you were here tonight, Jim.
We were supposed to do this together.

27:33.785 --> 27:35.912
And this is a picture of my son.

27:35.987 --> 27:40.856
A lot of people say he looks like me, but
I'm not quite sure he's that handsome.

27:41.326 --> 27:43.419
He's really something.

27:43.795 --> 27:45.786
- What's his name?
- Nathan.

27:46.531 --> 27:47.862
Hmm.

27:49.601 --> 27:51.296
MIA: Mine's a snow day.

27:52.037 --> 27:53.504
My happy place?

27:53.571 --> 27:56.199
Lindsey's is Walden Pond.
Mine's a snow day in Ohio.

27:56.274 --> 27:57.605
No school.

27:57.676 --> 27:59.405
MIA: I'd stay in bed under the warm covers,

27:59.477 --> 28:02.002
and my mom would bring me
hot chocolate.

28:02.080 --> 28:05.140
How about you, Peyton? Your mom ever
bring you hot chocolate on a snow day?

28:05.216 --> 28:06.979
No, I didn't have...

28:08.386 --> 28:10.547
I didn't have a whole lot of snow days.

28:10.622 --> 28:13.352
Brooke and I did build
a pretty killer snow fort once.

28:13.425 --> 28:17.361
And you sat in it, and you worried
that your lives were about to change.

28:17.429 --> 28:19.659
Just because you edited
a book about my life

28:19.731 --> 28:22.063
doesn't mean you know
anything about me.

28:22.133 --> 28:25.034
I didn't mean anything by it. I was just...

28:25.370 --> 28:27.270
It's a beautiful story.

28:27.906 --> 28:29.965
(STRUMMING GUITAR)

28:31.910 --> 28:33.502
That's nice, Mia.

28:33.578 --> 28:37.776
Thanks. I've had this melody forever
and just don't have the lyrics yet.

28:37.849 --> 28:40.079
Why don't you keep playing it
and maybe we can help you?

28:40.151 --> 28:43.120
I think maybe we should probably
just work on that in the studio, alone.

28:43.188 --> 28:46.385
Oh, for God's sakes.
What am I gonna do, steal Mia's song?

28:46.458 --> 28:48.722
I don't know. Songs? Friends?

28:48.993 --> 28:50.426
What about you, Scraggly?

28:50.495 --> 28:53.521
I heard you stole Lucas from Brooke once.
Pot, meet kettle.

28:53.598 --> 28:55.122
Ass, meet face.

28:56.234 --> 29:00.603
(SINGING) <i>Pot, meet kettle, ass, meet face</i>

29:01.139 --> 29:02.401
I don't think that's gonna work, guys.

29:02.474 --> 29:05.739
Wait. That's hot. No,
drop that bomb again. I got something.

29:05.810 --> 29:07.607
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

29:07.879 --> 29:09.176
- All right, ready?
- Okay.

29:09.247 --> 29:11.306
One, two, three, four.

29:11.382 --> 29:13.612
(RAPPING) <i>Straight from the ghetto</i>
<i>Packing wood like Geppetto</i>

29:13.685 --> 29:16.518
<i>Ain't gonna bathe</i>
<i>till I look like Jared Leto...</i>

29:16.588 --> 29:18.385
(BEATBOXING)

29:18.456 --> 29:19.980
- What?
- Nice.

29:20.358 --> 29:22.223
(ALL LAUGHING)

29:22.727 --> 29:24.490
Don't laugh at him.

29:25.964 --> 29:29.730
You're right. Creation versus criticism.
Let me try one.

29:32.837 --> 29:34.828
Two, three, four...

29:35.206 --> 29:37.834
(SINGING) <i>My name's Peyton</i>
<i>Fake-blonde Peyton</i>

29:37.909 --> 29:40.878
<i>I don't have a boyfriend</i>
<i>'cause I'm a bitch</i>

29:42.113 --> 29:43.205
(LAUGHS)

29:43.882 --> 29:45.213
Play it again, Mia.

29:45.283 --> 29:47.012
Guys, we need to stop.

29:47.085 --> 29:48.416
Mia.

29:48.787 --> 29:51.187
One, two, three, four...

29:51.623 --> 29:55.252
(SINGING) <i>Her name's Lindsey</i>
<i>Man-faced Lindsey</i>

29:55.393 --> 30:01.491
<i>And her fiancé proposed to me first</i>
<i>With the very same ring</i>

30:05.503 --> 30:07.494
- You're lying.
- Oh, you didn't know?

30:07.572 --> 30:09.904
- Peyton.
- No, is... Is she gonna cry?

30:09.974 --> 30:12.135
- Stop it.
- Go ahead, let's cry, little rich girl.

30:12.210 --> 30:14.269
- I said stop it.
- Is Daddy gonna throw you a great, big,

30:14.345 --> 30:16.939
huge wedding at Walden Pond
for his little crybaby daughter?

30:17.015 --> 30:18.482
Peyton, you don't know
what you're talking about.

30:18.550 --> 30:20.848
It's fine, Haley.
Daddy's gonna make everything better

30:20.919 --> 30:23.387
for the little rich girl
that got everything she ever wanted.

30:23.454 --> 30:25.786
He's dead. All right, Peyton?

30:25.857 --> 30:28.826
He's dead.
He died two years ago from cancer

30:28.893 --> 30:32.124
but not until he couldn't walk
or talk or even recognize me.

30:32.197 --> 30:35.689
Does that make you happy?
Does that make you feel better?

30:35.767 --> 30:37.928
That his death is with me every day,

30:38.002 --> 30:40.232
that I was the one
who had to turn off the ventilator

30:40.305 --> 30:43.138
because my mother
was too destroyed to do it?

30:43.208 --> 30:46.905
You want to hear the sound he made
before he took that last breath?

30:46.978 --> 30:51.142
Oh, 'cause I can still hear it,
exactly how it sounded.

30:54.085 --> 30:56.280
Oh, does that make you happy?

30:56.921 --> 31:00.049
- Are you glad that my life isn't perfect?
- Lindsey, I...

31:00.124 --> 31:03.252
I used to admire the Peyton from the book.

31:03.628 --> 31:07.291
She seemed so noble, kind.

31:10.802 --> 31:14.795
I wish she were here, Peyton.
That version of you.

31:16.641 --> 31:18.438
What happened to her?

31:30.021 --> 31:32.285
(PLAYING <i>WISH YOU WERE)</i>

31:48.139 --> 31:50.767
<i>MIA: (SINGING) I was true</i>

31:52.477 --> 31:55.742
<i>As the sky is blue</i>

31:56.581 --> 32:00.108
<i>But I couldn't soon</i>

32:01.219 --> 32:05.212
<i>Say the same for you</i>
<i>No, no</i>

32:05.290 --> 32:09.624
<i>So now I find</i>

32:09.694 --> 32:13.926
<i>Denial in my eyes</i>

32:13.998 --> 32:17.627
<i>I'm mesmerized by</i>

32:17.702 --> 32:22.366
<i>The picture that's in my mind</i>

32:23.541 --> 32:29.969
<i>Tell me when</i>
<i>I'll finally see your shallow heart</i>

32:30.048 --> 32:32.710
<i>For what it is</i>

32:32.784 --> 32:38.984
<i>'Cause I don't want to</i>
<i>keep on believing in illusions</i>

32:39.057 --> 32:41.116
<i>No, no, no</i>

32:41.192 --> 32:45.686
<i>'Cause I've seen your act</i>
<i>And I know all the facts</i>

32:45.763 --> 32:49.961
<i>I'm still in love with</i>
<i>Who I wish you were, yeah</i>

32:50.034 --> 32:54.266
<i>And it ain't hard to see</i>
<i>Who you are underneath</i>

32:54.339 --> 32:55.931
<i>I'm still in love with</i>

32:56.007 --> 32:58.202
<i>Who I wish you were</i>

32:58.276 --> 33:02.076
<i>I wish you were here</i>

33:07.285 --> 33:12.917
<i>I wish you were here</i>

33:24.202 --> 33:25.863
(THERE'S A REASON <i>PLA YING)</i>

33:25.937 --> 33:29.896
God, the last time I was trapped
in the school was the shooting.

33:34.078 --> 33:36.808
Do you know how
Lindsey and I got so close?

33:36.881 --> 33:41.784
She was editing Lucas' book,
and I still wasn't really sure about her,

33:41.853 --> 33:46.347
'cause I was rooting for Lucas
to be with my friend Peyton.

33:47.125 --> 33:48.956
Or maybe even Brooke.

33:53.031 --> 33:54.555
Anyway, she...

33:54.899 --> 33:59.097
She was working on the chapter
about the shooting, and she said to me,

33:59.170 --> 34:01.832
"I want this to be Lucas' best writing,

34:02.974 --> 34:06.171
"the best he has in him,
because Peyton deserves it.

34:09.347 --> 34:12.714
"Jimmy and Keith deserve it,
and that day deserves it."

34:17.621 --> 34:20.056
And we've been friends ever since.

34:33.603 --> 34:35.697
Can I please talk with you?

34:36.474 --> 34:39.237
I'm sorry. God, Lindsey, I'm sorry.

34:39.744 --> 34:42.235
I am so sorry for what I said
about your father, okay?

34:42.313 --> 34:44.713
I lost my mom to cancer, and I...

34:46.117 --> 34:47.447
I'm sorry.

34:48.652 --> 34:51.679
I don't know what it is, but for
whatever reason, you bring out

34:51.755 --> 34:56.386
the insecurities in me, and I end up being
the worst possible version of myself.

34:57.161 --> 34:58.924
Welcome to the club.

35:02.500 --> 35:04.730
Haley told me what you said about

35:04.802 --> 35:09.705
wanting to get that chapter right in the
book, the one about the school shooting.

35:10.108 --> 35:12.440
And I think that's what makes it so hard,

35:12.510 --> 35:16.037
you know, the fact that Lucas
has found this person that's so great

35:16.114 --> 35:18.344
and that has such a big heart.

35:20.351 --> 35:24.651
And it was never my ring,
I was just trying to hurt you.

35:25.623 --> 35:29.024
The only reason I recognized it
is 'cause that's the ring

35:29.093 --> 35:31.823
Keith gave Karen when he proposed to her

35:32.463 --> 35:36.297
